      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.26,
      "end": 10.22,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 11.26,
      "end": 17.42,
      "text": "Asop's Fables. The Traveler and His Dog. A Traveler was about to start on a journey",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.42,
      "end": 20.48,
      "text": "and said to his dog who was stretching himself by the door,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.1,
      "end": 26.54,
      "text": "Come, what are you yawning for? Hurry up and get ready. I mean you to go with me. But the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 26.54,
      "end": 31.74,
      "text": "dog merely wagged his tail and said quietly, I'm ready master, it's you I'm waiting for.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 32.78,
      "end": 35.1,
      "text": "End of the Traveler and His Dog.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
